# Largest Palindrome
### Description
Find the largest palindrome made from the product of two 3-digit
numbers.
### Ordinary Solution
such like this:
```
function check(num):
    original = num
    reversed = 0
    while num > 0:
        reversed = 10 * reversed + num % 10 
    return orginal == reversed

largestPalindrome = 0;
for(int i = 100; i < 1000; i++){
    for(int j = 100; j < 1000; j++){
        if(check(i * j)){
            largestPalindrome = max(largestPalindrome, i * j)
        }
    }
}
```
* About ***check()***: The above demostration of check() uses an algorithm about taking digits. It first reverses the num then check if it equals to the original num. String algorithm is suitable as well.
* brute-force search algorithm
### Optimizate the Burte-force Search Algorithm
* Since the purpose is to find the largest palindrome, we can reverse the loop order.( i & j from 999 to 100)
* The current method checks many numbers **multiple times**. To stop checking numbers like this we can assume i <= j, roughly **halving** the number of calculations needed.
* ***Special tips:*** About the formule P = i * j, consider the digits of P, **P must be at least 6 digits long.** Since this, we can let the digits of P be x, y and z.
![image][temp]
11 is prime, and 11 is a factor of P. In other words, as least one of the integers i or j have a factor of 11. Using this information we can determine what values of j we check depending on i:
```java
public class Solution04 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        long i = 9999999L;
        long largestPalindrome = 0;
        while (i >= 100) {
            long j;
            long downwards_step;
            if(i % 11 == 0){
                j = 9999999L;
                downwards_step = 1;
            }else{
                j = 9999990L;
                downwards_step = 11;
            }
            while (j >= i) {
                if (j * i < largestPalindrome) break;
                if (check(i * j)) {
                    largestPalindrome = i * j;
                }
                j -= downwards_step;
            }
            i--;
        }
        System.out.println(largestPalindrome);
    }

    public static boolean check(long num) {
        String str = String.valueOf(num);
        for (int i = 0; i < str.length() / 2; i++) {
            if (str.charAt(i) != str.charAt(str.length() - i - 1)) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```
